# BeagleBone — Data Controller

Processes sensor data from the sensor server, manages the SQLite database, handles UART communication, and drives heartbeat logic.

## Source Files

| File | Description |
|:-----|:------------|
| `data_controller.c` | Main controller loop |
| `commands.c` / `commands.h` | Command dispatch |
| `cmd_handler.c` | Command handler implementations |
| `db_manager.c` | SQLite database interface |
| `heartbeat.c` | Device heartbeat tracking |
| `uart_controller.c` | UART communication to STM32 targets |
| `shared_data.h` | Shared state structures |
| `controller_internal.h` | Internal types |
| `data-controller-wrapper.sh` | systemd wrapper script |

## Dependencies

```bash
sudo apt install libsqlite3-dev:armhf
```

## Build

```bash
cd beaglebone/controller
export ARCH=arm
export CROSS_COMPILE=arm-linux-gnueabihf-
${CROSS_COMPILE}gcc data_controller.c commands.c db_manager.c heartbeat.c \
  uart_controller.c cmd_handler.c -o data_controller \
  -lpthread -lrt -lsqlite3

# Verify architecture
file data_controller
# Expected: ELF 32-bit LSB pie executable, ARM...
```

## Deploy

```bash
scp data_controller debian@beaglebone.local:/home/debian/controller/
ssh debian@beaglebone.local "sudo systemctl restart sensor-server data-controller && sudo systemctl status sensor-server"
```

